<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The code casts tiny_body to a non-const void*: (void *) tiny_body is passed to MHD_create_response_from_buffer. If tiny_body is const-qualified (e.g. a string literal or declared const char[]), this cast discards the const qualifier and produces a pointer that does not point to a const-qualified type — a direct violation of MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13. (The cast effectively hides the constness required by the rule.)
</scenario>
